{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"alias":"wore-clasp-rasp","description":"# WS8 — Harden Gerrit auth (replace DEVELOPMENT_BECOME_ANY_ACCOUNT with GitHub OAuth)\n\n## Why\nThe live Gerrit (`rebar.solutions.navateam.com`, 3.14) runs `auth.type =\nDEVELOPMENT_BECOME_ANY_ACCOUNT` — a dev-only mode where anyone can impersonate any account (no\nreal IdP). It CANNOT be the sole gate on production GitHub `main` (WS7) until real auth is in\nplace. **Confirmed strategy (2026-07-01): GitHub OAuth via the `gerrit-oauth-provider` plugin\n(GitHub backend), no reverse-proxy org gate** — access curated via a short account roster + Gerrit\nACLs. Precedent: GerritHub authenticates its whole user base this way; the plugin is actively\nmaintained (3.13.x, tracks the Gerrit release train). Blocks WS7.\n\n## Config (the target state)\n`infra/compose/gerrit.config`:\n```ini\n[auth]\n    type = OAUTH\n    gitBasicAuthPolicy = HTTP        # bots + git-over-HTTP keep working via HTTP passwords\n[plugin \"gerrit-oauth-provider-github-oauth\"]\n    root-url = \"https://github.com/\"\n    client-id = \"<GitHub OAuth App client id>\"     # non-secret; from SSM\n```\n`etc/secure.config` (secrets, NOT committed — materialized from SSM like the S5 deploy key):\n```ini\n[plugin \"gerrit-oauth-provider-github-oauth\"]\n    client-secret = \"<GitHub OAuth App client secret>\"\n```\nPlus: install the pinned `gerrit-oauth-provider` jar into `$GERRIT_SITE/plugins`, and remove ALL\n`DEVELOPMENT_*` auth.\n\n## Deliverables — split by access boundary\n### In-repo (committed; applied on a fresh redeploy) — DELIVERABLE THIS SESSION\n- A runbook `infra/runbooks/gerrit-auth-hardening.md`: the full procedure (OAuth App, plugin,\n  gerrit.config/secure.config, SSM params, redeploy, bot HTTP-password provisioning, account\n  migration, verification, rollback).\n- `gerrit-oauth-provider` pinned-jar provenance in `infra/gerrit/plugins/README.md` +\n  install-plugins scaffolding.\n- The `[auth]` block comment in `infra/compose/gerrit.config` points at the runbook + WS8 (the\n  live flip to `type = OAUTH` lands with the plugin+secrets chain, per the runbook — flipping it\n  in isolation would break a fresh Gerrit boot).\n\n### Access-gated (needs org admin + working AWS) — HANDOFF\n- Create the **GitHub OAuth App** on `navapbc` (callback `https://rebar.solutions.navateam.com/oauth`)\n  → client-id/secret. (Needs GitHub org admin via the web UI; this session's token lacks `admin:org`.)\n- Put client-id/secret in **SSM** under the Gerrit secret prefix; add the params to `infra/terraform/ssm.tf`.\n- **Apply to the live host** (AWS SSM/SSH — this session's AWS session is EXPIRED): install the\n  plugin, seed the OAuth config into the live `site/etc/gerrit.config` + `secure.config`, remove\n  become-any-account, restart Gerrit.\n- **Provision bot credentials BEFORE cutover**: give the `rebar-review-bot` service account an HTTP\n  password (dev-mode required none), so its git/REST access survives the auth change.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n### In-repo (this session)\n- [ ] `infra/runbooks/gerrit-auth-hardening.md` documents the complete GitHub-OAuth hardening procedure (OAuth App → plugin → gerrit.config/secure.config → SSM → redeploy → bot passwords → account migration → verify → rollback).\n- [ ] The `gerrit-oauth-provider` jar is pinned + provenance-documented (plugins/README.md) and wired into the plugin install path.\n- [ ] `infra/compose/gerrit.config` `[auth]` comment points at the runbook + WS8 (records that the live flip to OAUTH lands with the plugin+secrets chain).\n### Live (access-gated)\n- [ ] GitHub OAuth App created; client-id/secret in SSM; `ssm.tf` params added.\n- [ ] Live Gerrit switched to `auth.type = OAUTH` (become-any-account removed); Gerrit restarts healthy; a human logs in via GitHub OAuth.\n- [ ] `rebar-review-bot` has an HTTP password; its REST/git access verified post-cutover.\n\n## Dependencies\n- Blocks WS7 (the Gerrit-only cutover must not precede real auth).\n- Live steps need `navapbc` GitHub org admin + working AWS access to the Gerrit host (d251 infra).","id":"f2d6-0e1a-3438-425b","parent_id":"b744-4fb9-2d05-4b49","priority":1,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"story","title":"WS8: Harden Gerrit auth (GitHub OAuth, replace DEVELOPMENT_BECOME_ANY_ACCOUNT)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1782881456125031001,"uuid":"2e347e91-c5de-48b1-a0d2-fea8ccc8341e"}